    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Folder, Models",
      "ShowInDocs": true,
      "GraphsPerPage": 6,
      "Name": "HydraulicConductance",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [
        {
          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Name": "Group notes",
          "Text": "Hydraulic-conductance scenarios: plant hydraulic conductance is varied under the same moderate-deficit irrigation regime. Current status: this scenario is demand-capped because potential root water supply exceeds water demand and actual supply remains approximately equal to demand. The test therefore checks hydraulic diagnostic behavior only: Kplant treatment order, plant-limited flags, total/reference conductance direction, and demand-capped detection. Realised uptake, allocation, fruit biomass, and growth variables remain in the report as diagnostic context, not hard response assertions.",
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        }
      ],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Folder, Models",
      "ShowInDocs": true,
      "GraphsPerPage": 6,
      "Name": "HydraulicGrowthResponse",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [
        {
          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Name": "Group notes",
          "Text": "Controlled hydraulic growth-response sensibility test: low and high Kplant treatments vary only plant hydraulic conductance. GenericFruitTree-local diagnostics (HydraulicPlantConductanceOutput, HydraulicKTermOutput, HydraulicPlantLimitedOutput, SupplyIndexEffectiveOutput, GrowthStressModifierOutput, leaf Fw, canopy/leaf biomass, and fruit biomass) are used to decide whether the local hydraulic stress pathway separates. PMF water arbitration outputs (WDemand, WSupply, and WAllocated) remain diagnostic context only. Under the current setup, if plant-limited diagnostics separate but SupplyIndexEffective/GrowthStressModifier or biomass do not, this scenario is classified as diagnostic-only: GenericFruitTree hydraulic conductance is not currently coupled strongly enough to realised growth here. This test is not empirical validation and does not validate PMF water uptake.",
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        }
      ],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Folder, Models",
