          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Name": "Group notes",
          "Text": "Reserve scenarios: one-axis capacity, storage-rate, mobilisation-rate, and source/sink treatments check reserve diagnostics directly rather than fruit or yield response. The generic orchard scaffold keeps perennial structural wood from decaying without replacement and from being moved to residue at seasonal harvest/reset, so reserve capacity remains interpretable. This is a scaffold/perennial-biomass correction, not reserve-physics tuning.",
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        }
